snippet.textDisplay: I had the Mother in Law from HELL, and my Husband didn’t have the balls, quite frankly, to stand up to her.  She reminded me of the Mother on “Everybody Loves Raymond” (Raymond’s mother) with the awful bleach blond hair, the tacky home, the constant put downs about Deborah’s cooking and house work, only not as smart & strong as her and a lousy cook.  Her name was Claire, and I used to like that name until I met this woman.  She was whiny, manipulative, and she would fake heart attacks if she picked fights and if I dared to fight back.  Needless to say, the marriage didn’t last—she said I was a “spoiled little Bitch” because my parents were paying for me to go to College, UC Santa Barbara, and I met him in Orange County when I took a year off to work and make some money.  They expected me to quit like Gil quit college (Long Beach State)—his parents had moved here from Canada and didn’t think getting a College degree was necessary (which tells you what kind of people they were). If I was nice to her, she said I was phony.  If I acted like myself, she said I was spoiled.  My so-called Husband wouldn’t stand up to her, and he became a “born again Christian” and was impossible to live with.  He couldn’t be trusted to pay the rent because he’s give all his money to his new Chirch.  I had to divorce him after 6 years.
